headline: Crypto bulls were amped for potential solana ETF approvals this week. But the government shutdown threw it into limbo.
summary: Crypto bulls have been buzzing with anticipation that several major Wall Street firms may win approval to launch exchange-traded funds investing in solana, a lesser-known crypto, as soon as this week, but a partial U.S. government shutdown has thrown the process into limbo.

headline: Volatility Index Surges After Trump Tariff Threat
summary: Trade tensions are ratcheting up Wall Street’s fear gauge. The CBOE Market Volatility Index soared 32% in Friday trading after President Trump posted on social media that he is considering "a massive increase in tariffs" on Chinese products.

headline: Cboe Global Markets (CBOE): Assessing Valuation After Securing Australian Regulatory Approval for IPO Listings
summary: Cboe Global Markets (CBOE) has secured regulatory approval from the Australian Securities & Investments Commission to operate a stock listings market in Australia.
